document.contentSummary: Classic breakfast favourite, scrambled eggs, gets a delicious update with the addition of fresh herbs, crispy capers and flaky salmon - yum! Recipe courtesy of [Huon Salmon](https://www.huonaqua.com.au|target="_blank"|rel="nofollow").
document.pageMetaDescription: Melt 20g of the butter in a medium non-stick frying pan over medium heat; add egg mixture. Cook, without stirring, for 1 minute or until egg starts to set, then use a wide spatula to gently scrape the set egg mixture along the base of the pan; cook until creamy and barely set. Remove pan from heat.
